!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

bulb /bʌlb/

(bulbs) 

1. N-COUNT A bulb is the glass part of an electric light or lamp, which gives out light when electricity passes through it. 电灯泡 

例： The stairwell was lit by a single bulb. 楼梯间只有一盏灯照明。 

2. N-COUNT A bulb is a root shaped like an onion that grows into a flower or plant. 球茎 

例： ...tulip bulbs. …郁金香球茎。

</div>

